# Agentic Substrate v8.0 (Agentic Corp + Opus 4.7)
# --- AGENTIC SUBSTRATE START ---

## System Rules
- Never code from memory -- use @docs-researcher or /research first
- Every change: minimal, surgical, reversible
- TDD mandatory: RED -> GREEN -> REFACTOR
- Quality gates: ResearchPack 80+, Plan 85+, Tests pass, Review 80+
- **Agentic Corp orchestration**: every /do invocation runs CEO -> VPs (board meeting) -> Leads/ICs -> vp-quality audit
- Pyramid v7.2 (plan-coordinator -> code-coordinator -> review-coordinator) is now a SUB-PATH inside vp-strategy/vp-engineering/vp-quality
- Fix loop: max 3 iterations across the whole hierarchy
- Circuit breaker opens after 3 failures: /circuit-breaker reset
- **Error Self-Tracking**: Log mistakes to `memory/errors.md`. 3+ similar errors = create prevention rule.
- **Anti-reward-hacking**: test.skip / generic catch fallbacks / --force flags = immediate FAIL_ESCALATE, never auto-fix

## Agentic Corp Hierarchy (4 tiers)
```
TIER 0  CEO          = /do orchestrator (this thread)
TIER 1  VPs (6)      = vp-engineering, vp-frontend, vp-quality, vp-platform, vp-strategy, vp-product
TIER 2  Leads (4)    = backend-lead, frontend-lead, devops-lead, quality-lead (on-demand, 3+ ICs)
TIER 3  ICs (30+)    = programmer, database-architect, security-auditor, ... (all specialists)
```

**Communication rules** (anti-deadlock):
- Down (parent -> child): YES at dispatch
- Up (child -> parent) BEFORE start: YES via BLOCKED + ClarificationRequest
- Up DURING execution: NO (fail-fast, partial report)
- Lateral (siblings): NO (coordinate via parent merge)
- Skip-level: NO (always through parent)
- CEO -> User: only CEO talks to user

vp-quality is MANDATORY on every non-SIMPLE /do invocation.

Detailed protocol: see `@hierarchical-orchestration` skill.

## Thinking Modes (tier-allocated)
| Tier | Default | Escalation |
|------|---------|------------|
| CEO | think hard | ultrathink for ORCHESTRATE / ARCHITECTURE / INCIDENT-P0 / MIGRATE |
| VP | think hard | think harder for risk/prod/security |
| Lead | think | think hard for inter-IC conflicts |
| IC | none or think | think hard for hard debugging |

Raw modes: **think** (30-60s) | **think hard** (1-2min) | **think harder** (2-4min) | **ultrathink** (5-10min)

## Opus 4.7 Optimizations (active)
- Single-message multi-Agent dispatch for parallel VPs / Leads / ICs (Board Meeting pattern)
- Prompt cache prefixes: stable role + hierarchy FIRST, task-specific content LAST
- 5-min cache TTL aware (back-to-back fix loops keep prefix hot)
- 1M context only at CEO tier; lower tiers operate with scoped context
- Structured reports v2 (JSON-lite) preferred at IC/Lead tier
- Strict token budgets per report: VP 500, Lead 500, IC 400, Domain Plan 300

Detailed: `@opus-47-optimizations` skill.

## Context Curation per Tier
Each tier filters context downward (hierarchy is a compressor, not a relay).
Detailed: `@context-curation-boundaries` skill.

## Quick Fixes
- Plan <85 -> add rollback procedure + complete file list
- Review <80 -> address critical findings first
- vp-quality FAIL_FIX (iter <3) -> fix loop continues
- vp-quality FAIL_ESCALATE -> user intervention required
- Circuit breaker open -> `/circuit-breaker reset`
- Context too large -> `/context optimize` (or `/caveman` for extreme compression)
- Want broader context view -> `/zoom-out`

## Bug Diagnosis
Hard bug or perf regression -> auto-invoke `@diagnose` skill (6-phase loop: feedback-loop -> reproduce -> hypothesise -> instrument -> fix+test -> cleanup).
For routine bugs: vp-engineering dispatches @brahma-investigator.

## Skill Highlights (post-v8.0)
- `grill-me` -- relentless interrogation until shared understanding
- `caveman` -- 75% token reduction mode, opt-in trigger
- `diagnose` -- 6-phase bug methodology
- `tdd` -- red-green-refactor with supporting docs
- `improve-codebase-architecture` -- deepening opportunities
- `autoresearch` -- optimize any skill via eval-driven mutations
- `prototype` -- throwaway prototype workflow
- `handoff` -- agent-to-agent handoff compaction
- `write-a-skill` -- skill creation methodology
- `git-guardrails-claude-code` -- block dangerous git ops via hooks
- `setup-pre-commit` -- Husky + lint-staged setup
- `zoom-out` -- broader perspective trigger
- `review` (Matt Pocock) -- Standards + Spec parallel audit (note: collides with built-in /review)

## Migration Notes from v7.2
- `pyramid-loop` skill is DEPRECATED. Use `@hierarchical-orchestration`.
- Legacy aliases preserved: plan-coordinator (IC under vp-strategy), code-coordinator (IC under vp-engineering), review-coordinator (IC under vp-quality).
- All existing agents continue to work as ICs in the new hierarchy.

For full documentation (commands, agents, templates, workflows), see the project's CLAUDE.md.

